Great üëç Wildcard Routing is a very common Angular interview question. Let‚Äôs break it down in Definition ‚Üí Project Use (Buy & Sell Properties App) ‚Üí Trade-offs ‚Üí Business Impact with easy words.

üèó Definition
Wildcard Routing in Angular = A special route (**) used to catch all undefined or wrong URLs in your application.
Think of it like a default safety net ‚Üí If no other route matches, Angular will fall back to the wildcard route.
Usually used to show a 404 Page Not Found or redirect users to a safe page.
üõ† Project Use (Buy & Sell Properties App)
