Suppose valid routes are:
/properties ‚Üí shows property list
/property/:id ‚Üí shows property details
/login ‚Üí login page
üëâ Now if a user types:

/xyz or /random-link (which doesn‚Äôt exist)
üëâ Wildcard route (**) catches it and shows ‚Üí ‚Äú‚ùå Page Not Found‚Äù
Code Example:

const routes: Routes = [
  { path: 'properties', component: PropertyListComponent },
  { path: 'property/:id', component: PropertyDetailComponent },
  { path: 'login', component: LoginComponent },
  
